 Code Submission Guidelines 
1. Participants must submit: 
○ Complete source code 
○ Supporting files (if any) 
○ A README file containing: 
■ Problem statement 
■ System architecture / approach 
■ Steps to execute the code 
2. The code must strictly follow the official submission template provided on the 
official website of IEEE RGIPT SB ( https://www.ieeergipt.in/ ) 
3. Only the provided template must be used. 
○ Submissions not following the template will not be evaluated. 
4. File naming format: 
TeamName_Phase2.zip 
5. AI Usage Policy 
1. Direct copy-paste from AI tools is strictly restricted. 
2. Participants may use AI tools only for reference or learning, not for generating 
complete solutions. 
3. Any submission found to be fully AI-generated or copied will lead to immediate 
disqualification. 
4. Participants must be able to clearly explain and justify their code during the live 
presentation.